voice_to_text: I was like to bring up this challenge when someone talks about intuitive eating or calorie counting is hard or using a calorie tracker is hard or they don't like it or things like of that nature because I used to use that excuse I used to get severe anxiety when using a calorie counting app and it's just because it's new you know a lot of people don't do it and the thing I like to bring up to someone if they say intuitive eating versus tracking I give them this challenge track your calories for a week two weeks right get used to it get comfortable with it and then take like two three four days and intuitively eat right but write down what you're eating don't track it but write down what you're eating and then at the end of the day when you're getting close to going to bed and you're done with your eating for the day log the foods you wrote down into the same app and watch how much more your calories are over than when you're on track you're weighing and you're tracking correctly but that's just my two cents and it's a little fun challenge to actually see how bad everyone is at decimating when it comes to food intake and calorie intake so anyways much love god bless have a wonderful day
